After a long stagnation, the number of Fidesz sympathizers has grown significantly until the beginning of December. For the first time since 2002, the party has had the largest base camp, while approval for the socialists has reached an unprecedented low of 13 percent, according to Gallup.
The difference is clear for the loyal voters thanks to the high determination of the opposition supporters: more than two-thirds (71 percent) are opposed to one-fifth (20 percent) of the vote for the MSZP.
