After more hopeful outlooks in spring and summer, families again see the change in their financial situation more pessimistic.
For the coming year, the majority of the population expects a further deterioration in the situation; only a tenth is expected to improve.
A Gallup poll conducted in December found that 71% of respondents — a historic high — rated the prime minister’s work as “rather bad than right.”
