The Institute’s “Risk Warning Report” states, among other things, that in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the “enhancing of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsies and non-Gypsies population in Hungary, which could even be eliminated in the short term.
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provoking such an argument, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungarian opposition."
It is believed that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favour extremes, and increase the likelihood of violent clashes.
