The Congress approves the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Congressional resolution in the Senate on the amendments to the draft, the government published the provisions emanating from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senators who had pursued in their negotiations and votes the goal of establishing the best possible regulation that guarantees the safety of investors and regulates the activities of individual entrepreneurs.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, the MIFID, which redefines the Securities Services Regulation, seeks to improve investor protection, to increase the control requirement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and to promote cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive makes it possible to offer financial advice to both specialised companies and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the creation of new financial services companies (ESIS) to the consulting companies that combine with the investment and brokerage companies of securities.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that the multilateral systems of the effects business and the systems for the internationalisation of trading orders are added to the regulated circulation markets, which would eventually enter into competition with the current economic players.
The law obliges investment firms to declare the focus of their corporate profile, the confrontation and forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Economic Commission of the Congress subsequently made further changes, with the decision that the debt prescription with titles now have to be considered as a complex financial means for the investor due to its high degree of risk, confirmed by the U.S. mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the Legal Limitation of the Work Areas of Graduate Economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation, which restricted the work areas reserved for economists, was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a foreign basis, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for the acquisition of customers at the same time several investment companies.
The Harmonized Consumer Price Index (VPI) rose by five-tenths in November and is now at 4.1%.
The indicator, used by Eurostat to assess inflation rates within the European Union, provides the average price development in Spain in November.
Its publication is in line with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which, by disclosing the data, aim to compare local and quality products to US products.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared in advance by applying the same procedure as the harmonised consumer price index, but at the same time using various other statistical modelling methods to estimate the information not available at the time of calculation.
However, the Spanish Statistical Office (INE) cautioned that the pre-determined indicator only serves as a guide value and therefore does not have to match the final result, which will be announced on 14 December.
The Consumer Price Index (CPI) will continue to remain at a relatively high level
According to Deputy Head of Government and Minister of Economy and Finance Pedro Solbes, the rise of the VPI in November was a temporary development; at the same time, he assured that the price index would continue to remain at a relatively high level in the coming months.
However, Solbes noted in the halls of the congressional building that even if the current figure is not good, Spain’s inflation difference to the other members of the monetary union has remained more or less the same in recent years.
In addition, he stated that there were fewer surprises in November than in the previous month, during which the government did not expect such a high increase.
We expected a value of around 4% , the Minister of Economy and Finance announced with regard to the forecast published today.
