Which insurance is best for me?
The KFZ insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost expense, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right KFZ insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, one must be clear about what we are dealing with here.
An auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance company.
This Agreement shall be concluded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the Company shall receive the agreed insurance premium and, in return, is obliged to provide the corresponding amount of relief in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that even higher contribution payments are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women need to make less contribution payments, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same is true for married persons, since, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single people.
The benefit that is measured to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequently the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, the insurances must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly to choose the exact car insurance that meets his personal needs most often.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under the age of 25 are faced with numerous obstacles when choosing a low-priced insurance, such as low driving practice and young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance coverage to complete a full-cash insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Careful drivers can choose a full cascade with self-interest, so that the benefits of a full cascade insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage itself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the lower the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europe, a brokerage firm for online insurance.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage caused by the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs, so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes a fee referred to as an increase.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its earnings.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the driver to conclude a contract, due to the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most sensible to opt for full casco insurance with self-interest.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish leader of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year after the fear of the beginner has been put off.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out a full cash cover insurance; of course, only if it also allows the financial situation of the respective person.
On the insurers’ side, couples with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a fully co-insurance with self-insurance (in the amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which is used only for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive overall more relaxed and possess a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a fully-funded self-insurance (in the amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which is only used in case of a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it has high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
